CH15

Then Jason gave up his spirit in peace, saying, “Into Your hands, O YHWH, I commit my spirit,” and he was gathered to his fathers, having finished the race and kept the faith. The brothers buried him with great honor, glorifying YHWH for all the wonders wrought through him.
And many were added to the faith because of the testimony of Jason, who had received the apostles and opened his house to the word of life. His name became a blessing among the churches.
Jason stood firm before the rulers and said: “There is another King, Yeshua the Anointed.” And though they dragged him before the city authorities, he did not deny the Lord. Many believed because of his boldness.
Thus Jason and those with him completed their testimony in Thessalonica and Berea, and the word of the Lord spread throughout Macedonia and Achaia. They healed the sick and proclaimed the kingdom with power.
The Lord strengthened Jason and his household, and they became a refuge for the saints. Through him many turned from idols to serve the living and true God.
This is the gospel according to Jason, a fellow worker with Paul and Silas, who received the word with joy and suffered for the name of Yeshua the Anointed.

CH14

The grace of our Lord Yeshua the Anointed be with all who read these words. Amen.
Jason gave thanks to the Lord and said: “I have finished the work You gave me. Now receive my spirit.” And he fell asleep in the Lord, full of years and good works.
Then the Lord received Jason into His rest, for he had fought the good fight and kept the faith. Many were converted through his testimony, and the word of YHWH spread greatly.
And after they had borne witness in many cities and suffered many things for the name of Yeshua the Anointed, they came to the place appointed for them.
And thus Jason and his companions finished their course with joy, glorifying YHWH who had strengthened them through many trials. They departed in peace, having proclaimed the kingdom in all the regions they passed through.
While they were in the city of the Thessalonians, Jason was dragged before the rulers of the city and accused of harboring men who turned the world upside down. Yet he stood firm in the faith, proclaiming that Yeshua the Anointed is King, and many believed because of his bold testimony.
In Berea, the brethren searched the Scriptures daily with Jason to confirm these things, and many believed, both of the Jews and of the Greeks.
When they came to Thessalonica, Jason received Paul and Silas into his house, and the word of the Lord spread rapidly among the Gentiles.
While they journeyed through Macedonia and Achaia, Jason and his fellow laborers healed the sick and cast out demons in the name of Yeshua, and great fear fell upon all who heard these things.

